───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MODULE 1: UNDERSTANDING AI AGENTS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1.1 WHAT IS AN AI AGENT?
─────────────────────────
An AI agent is software that uses artificial intelligence to:
• Perceive its environment (read emails, browse web, receive commands)
• Make decisions based on goals and context
• Take actions autonomously
• Learn and improve over time
• Operate 24/7 without human intervention

Think of it as a digital employee that never sleeps, never takes breaks,
and can handle multiple tasks simultaneously.

1.2 TYPES OF AI AGENTS
───────────────────────
REACTIVE AGENTS
• Respond to immediate stimuli
• No memory of past interactions
• Best for: Simple, repetitive tasks

DELIBERATIVE AGENTS
• Use planning and reasoning
• Maintain internal state
• Best for: Complex decision-making

LEARNING AGENTS
• Improve from experience
• Adapt to user preferences
• Best for: Personalized experiences

AUTONOMOUS AGENTS
• Operate independently
• Self-managing goals
• Best for: Running businesses 24/7

