MODULE 4: MEMORY AND LEARNING SYSTEMS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

4.1 HOW AGENTS LEARN
─────────────────────
Agents learn through:

1. EXPLICIT FEEDBACK
   User tells agent what it did wrong
   "That response was too formal, be casual"

2. IMPLICIT FEEDBACK
   Agent infers from outcomes
   User didn't open the email → adjust subject

3. PATTERN RECOGNITION
   Agent notices recurring situations
   "Every time X happens, Y works best"

4. SELF-REFLECTION
   Agent reviews its own performance
   Weekly analysis of successes/failures

4.2 THE LEARNING LOOP
─────────────────────
┌─────────────┐
│   ACT       │  ← Take action
└──────┬──────┘
       │
       ▼
┌─────────────┐
│  OBSERVE    │  ← Watch results
└──────┬──────┘
       │
       ▼
┌─────────────┐
│  ANALYZE    │  ← What worked?
└──────┬──────┘
       │
       ▼
┌─────────────┐
│  ADAPT      │  ← Improve for next time
└──────┬──────┘
       │
       ▼
┌─────────────┐
│   STORE     │  ← Remember the lesson
└─────────────┘

