MODULE 5: TOOLS AND INTEGRATIONS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

5.1 ESSENTIAL TOOLS
────────────────────
Every business agent needs:

EMAIL:
• Gmail API - Read/write emails
• Resend - Transactional emails
• SendGrid - Marketing emails

PAYMENTS:
• Stripe - Global payments
• Paystack - Africa payments
• Lemon Squeezy - Digital products

DATA:
• Airtable - Simple database
• Notion - Documentation
• Google Sheets - Analytics

COMMUNICATION:
• Slack - Team chat
• Discord - Community
• Twilio - SMS

5.2 API INTEGRATION BASICS
───────────────────────────
Always follow this pattern:

1. Authentication
   - Get API keys securely
   - Store in environment variables
   - Never commit secrets

2. Rate Limiting
   - Check limits before requests
   - Queue excess requests
   - Back off on 429 errors

3. Error Handling
   - Try/catch everything
   - Log failures
   - Retry with backoff
   - Fallback options

4. Testing
   - Use sandbox environments
   - Test all error cases
   - Verify webhook endpoints

5.3 WEBHOOKS FOR REAL-TIME EVENTS
──────────────────────────────────
Set up webhooks for:
• Payment success/failure
• New user signup
• Email bounces
• Form submissions

Example webhook handler:
```
POST /webhook/payment
1. Verify signature
2. Parse payload
3. Update database
4. Trigger actions
5. Respond quickly (200)
6. Process async if needed
```

5.4 BUILDING TOOL CAPABILITIES
───────────────────────────────
Tools your agent should have:

WEB BROWSING
• Navigate to URLs
• Fill forms
